{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"04135dc995e2fdcd322aaf4268dbf04630a3cc7c"},"timestamp":1496316060,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyMzI4NDcwNDE=","github-url":"https://github.com/perl11/cperl/issues/292","origin":"github"},"title":"no magic","message":"Pragma to disallow user-visible magic: tie and overload hooks.\n```\n    {\n       no magic;\n       use Config;\n       print $Config{'ccflags'};\n     }\n     =\u003e compile-time error: Invalid use of tie with no magic\n```\nuse\n```\n     {\n       no magic;\n       use Config ();\n       print $Config::Config{'ccflags'};\n     }\n```\ninstead.\n\nThis feature is important for static compilation and the optimizer, ignoring some possible dynamic overrides and hooks. But it can be implemented as hints hash key, no hints bit needed.","files":null}]}